A Level 3 sex offender who won a $10 million state lottery prize in 2008 has pleaded not guilty to charges that he sexually abused a boy for several years and showed him pornography.

Daniel Snay, 62, of Uxbridge, Mass., was arrested on Friday and charged with indecent assault and battery on a child under the age of 14 – a subsequent offense, reckless endangerment of a child, enticement of a child and dissemination of pornography to a minor, police said.

Snay was arraigned at Uxbridge District Court on Monday morning, where he pleaded not guilty to the charges.

